The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for iris recognition, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for segmentation suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of the Mask R-CNN framework indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM), which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR), as iris recognition is often used as a biometric authentication technique.
